WEBVTT

00:20.891 --> 00:24.227
[**]

00:24.294 --> 00:27.363
[CHANTING]

01:08.138 --> 01:11.608
[**]

01:24.287 --> 01:25.889
[SIGHS]

01:29.592 --> 01:33.363
Ma! SeÃ±ora Nunez came in.
She's burning up with fever.

01:33.429 --> 01:36.532
Go cool her head.
Recite the 23rd Psalm.

01:36.599 --> 01:38.001
I'll be there in a bit.

01:50.213 --> 01:53.917
New Mexico, 1885

01:55.418 --> 01:57.387
"Though I walk through the
valley of the shadow of death,

01:57.453 --> 01:58.521
I fear no evil."

01:58.588 --> 01:59.890
Morning, kids.

01:59.956 --> 02:01.658
"Thou art with me.
Thy rod and staff...

02:01.725 --> 02:02.726
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

02:02.793 --> 02:04.728
"...they comfort me.

02:04.795 --> 02:06.529
"Thou preparest a table
before me

02:06.596 --> 02:08.464
"in the presence
of mine enemies.

02:08.531 --> 02:11.401
"Thou anointest my head with
oil. My cup runneth over.

02:11.467 --> 02:13.003
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

02:13.069 --> 02:14.404
"Surely goodness and mercy

02:14.470 --> 02:16.506
"shall follow me
all the days of my life.

02:16.572 --> 02:18.108
"And I will dwell
in the house--

02:18.174 --> 02:21.778
Darling,
get me some Cocea paste
and my tooth plier, please.

02:21.845 --> 02:23.113
Yes, ma'am.

02:23.179 --> 02:27.050
[SPEAKING SPANISH]

02:28.685 --> 02:30.086
No. No.

02:30.153 --> 02:33.990
[CONVERSING IN SPANISH]

02:34.057 --> 02:37.127
She don't worry
about the pain. No.

02:37.193 --> 02:40.596
It is her only tooth.
She worry how she look.

02:40.663 --> 02:41.664
Thank you.

02:41.732 --> 02:43.633
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

02:49.439 --> 02:50.974
Thank you.

02:51.674 --> 02:53.576
No! No, no!

02:53.643 --> 02:58.181
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

02:58.248 --> 03:00.784
I gonna need you to hold
your grandmother down.

03:00.851 --> 03:04.420
Darling, can you
hold her arm?

03:04.487 --> 03:07.557
Pin that, Dot. Hold her nose.
Hold her nose.

03:07.623 --> 03:10.426
[SPANISH CONTINUES]

03:12.628 --> 03:14.230
Careful.

03:23.106 --> 03:24.607
[SCREAMING]

03:24.674 --> 03:26.409
Gracias.

03:26.476 --> 03:28.945
[OLD WOMAN GROANING]

03:34.617 --> 03:37.487
I hate to ask...

03:37.553 --> 03:39.222
but can you
pay me for this today?

03:39.289 --> 03:41.691
[CURSES IN SPANISH]

03:48.531 --> 03:50.366
[ANIMAL SCREAMS]

03:52.068 --> 03:53.069
[GUNSHOT]

03:53.136 --> 03:54.137
[WHIMPERING]

03:54.204 --> 03:56.272
[GUN COCKS]

03:56.339 --> 03:59.976
Jumping pinches coyotes
sons of bitches.

04:00.043 --> 04:01.878
That lightning sure did
kill her.

04:01.945 --> 04:04.380
[COW MOOS]

04:04.447 --> 04:06.282
[HORSE WHINNIES]

04:09.252 --> 04:11.454
This calf ain't gonna
last the night out here.

04:11.521 --> 04:14.490
Let's put her in the barn.

04:16.392 --> 04:17.793
SeÃ±or Brake.

04:24.801 --> 04:26.436
Indian.

04:26.502 --> 04:28.671
Apache, maybe.

04:28.738 --> 04:32.608
Some kind of Apache
son of a bitch.

04:33.609 --> 04:37.113
[**]

04:53.196 --> 04:55.165
BRAKE: Good day, sir.

04:58.935 --> 05:01.237
I said, hello.

05:03.639 --> 05:06.609
That your man over there
in the trees?

05:11.747 --> 05:16.319
What is he planning on doing
with that carbine?

05:16.386 --> 05:18.788
We've had trouble
with coyotes killing calves.

05:18.855 --> 05:21.892
Tell him I'm not a coyote.

05:21.958 --> 05:23.393
[WHISTLES]

05:29.765 --> 05:31.134
Is that the healer's place?

05:32.135 --> 05:33.536
BRAKE: You come for doctoring?

05:49.452 --> 05:52.555
[COWS MOOING]

06:00.630 --> 06:02.665
BRAKE: Lady shuts her doors
at sundown.

06:04.200 --> 06:06.402
She's pretty firm
about her hours.

06:06.469 --> 06:07.837
You're welcome
to spend the night,

06:07.904 --> 06:09.805
see her in the morning,
though.

06:09.872 --> 06:11.474
I thank you kindly.

06:17.847 --> 06:19.815
Barn's this way, mister.

06:43.239 --> 06:46.609
There's a spare bunk
over there, Mr...

06:46.676 --> 06:48.344
Mr. Fernandez.

06:50.113 --> 06:53.583
Jones. The man that owned
that saddle tried to kill me.

06:53.649 --> 06:55.351
I was living with
the Jicarilla at the time.

06:55.418 --> 06:57.853
I suppose he thought
I was one of them.

06:57.920 --> 06:59.089
You're Apache, huh?

06:59.155 --> 07:00.690
[MUTTERS IN SPANISH]

07:00.756 --> 07:02.058
What did you say?

07:02.125 --> 07:03.626
Forget it.

07:03.693 --> 07:05.428
What did you say?

07:05.495 --> 07:07.630
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

07:07.697 --> 07:10.100
[REPLIES IN SPANISH]

07:13.736 --> 07:15.305
Come over here.

07:18.074 --> 07:19.409
Now, I mean it!

07:20.810 --> 07:23.379
There'll be no trouble here.

07:23.446 --> 07:26.682
If that's too tough for you to
understand, you can move on.

07:39.462 --> 07:41.031
[HORSE SNORTS]

07:43.766 --> 07:45.168
Emiliano, unpack his mule.

07:45.235 --> 07:49.305
You will keep your hands
off of my mule...

07:49.372 --> 07:51.941
Emiliano.

08:10.093 --> 08:11.794
[DOOR OPENS]

08:11.861 --> 08:13.229
Don't slam that door.

08:13.296 --> 08:14.464
BRAKE: Yes, ma'am.

08:14.530 --> 08:16.066
You know there are houses
in Cleveland

08:16.132 --> 08:17.733
with lamps that run
on electricity.

08:17.800 --> 08:20.136
I'd like to see Cleveland.

08:28.744 --> 08:30.146
Can you fetch the water,
please, Dot?

08:30.213 --> 08:31.214
DOT: Yes, ma'am.

08:35.118 --> 08:39.621
At the fair, there's gonna be
expositions of the future.

08:39.688 --> 08:41.057
There's gonna be
a graphophone.

08:41.124 --> 08:43.958
You can hear
your own voice back on it.

08:44.025 --> 08:45.495
The Dickersons are going.

08:45.561 --> 08:46.796
Brake can't spare you.

08:48.164 --> 08:49.165
Ma.

08:49.232 --> 08:50.833
Not tomorrow
with the cows calving.

08:50.900 --> 08:52.202
The Fosters too.

08:52.268 --> 08:55.271
Got all the future
you need right here.

08:55.338 --> 08:58.508
Riding all day with this
cramping and all.

09:07.717 --> 09:09.719
Don't you ever act
helpless and pitiable

09:09.785 --> 09:11.287
to win favor with a man.

09:11.354 --> 09:13.456
Some people shouldn't give
advice on how to act with men.

09:15.591 --> 09:17.593
And it's "pitiful," not
"pitiable" in English.

09:17.660 --> 09:19.929
You heard what I said.

09:20.863 --> 09:22.498
That pail's half-empty.

09:22.565 --> 09:23.833
I didn't do it.

09:23.899 --> 09:26.469
It's that old Indian's
dumb old mule.

09:26.536 --> 09:27.703
What Indian?

09:27.770 --> 09:29.772
Some drifter
looking for doctoring.

09:31.574 --> 09:33.509
If you're gonna eat
barefoot...

09:33.576 --> 09:36.146
why don't you take supper
with the animals in the barn.

09:36.212 --> 09:39.982
My boots don't fit no more.
Cut off my blood circulation.

09:40.049 --> 09:41.617
It's your birthday soon.

09:41.684 --> 09:43.686
I'll have gangrene by then.

09:43.753 --> 09:45.955
Your mother may just have to
saw off your feet, then.

09:46.021 --> 09:47.557
Like poor old Mr. Swenson.

09:47.623 --> 09:50.025
[LAUGHING]

09:55.030 --> 09:56.866
Mr. Jones.

09:58.501 --> 10:01.237
Maggie, this is the visiting
gentleman I mentioned.

10:03.439 --> 10:06.242
I'll bet a warm meal
sounds pretty good to you.

10:07.643 --> 10:09.412
Magdalena.

10:23.058 --> 10:26.996
I'm afraid we have
just enough food for family.

10:27.062 --> 10:28.898
We can't be offering
our hospitality tonight.

10:31.534 --> 10:34.069
I'm sure we can all do with
a little less on out plate.

10:34.136 --> 10:36.272
MAGGIE: I'm quite sure
we can't!

10:36.339 --> 10:39.542
I have two growing girls
to feed.

10:39.609 --> 10:41.277
Maggie?

10:45.515 --> 10:46.516
Maggie.

10:54.023 --> 10:57.026
Lilly,
why don't you say grace.

11:10.673 --> 11:12.542
Who is he?

11:15.278 --> 11:18.514
Called you Magdalena.

11:18.581 --> 11:21.317
Your hair bristles
when you lay eyes on him.

11:21.384 --> 11:22.885
He scares me, is all.

11:24.186 --> 11:25.621
Nobody scares you.

11:25.688 --> 11:27.623
Can't trust him.

11:27.690 --> 11:30.293
Maggie, who is he?

11:39.001 --> 11:41.304
He's my father.

11:46.376 --> 11:47.643
I thought your father
was dead.

11:47.710 --> 11:49.645
He is.

11:49.712 --> 11:51.814
To me, he is.

11:53.483 --> 11:55.117
I want him gone, Brake.

11:55.184 --> 11:56.452
You want him gone?

11:56.519 --> 11:57.987
He's your kin.
You just can't--

11:58.053 --> 12:01.957
He ran off when I wasn't
Dot's age. Went Indian.

12:02.024 --> 12:05.060
Turn your back, he'll eat
your horses and dogs.

12:05.127 --> 12:08.030
He's being chased...

12:08.097 --> 12:11.100
or running from something,
I don't know what.

12:11.166 --> 12:14.370
But he's bad, Brake.
I swear.

12:14.437 --> 12:17.807
I do not want him
near my children.

12:20.910 --> 12:25.214
We're Indians, Lilly.
We're Indians.

12:26.782 --> 12:29.852
[SNORING]

12:35.858 --> 12:37.360
Does he do that all night?

12:38.628 --> 12:40.496
Oh, he's just getting started.

12:40.563 --> 12:41.964
You come here for the healing?

12:42.031 --> 12:44.400
In a manner of speaking.

12:44.467 --> 12:46.802
Thought you might be hungry.

12:46.869 --> 12:49.472
It's rabbit stew.
I can't eat rabbits.

12:49.539 --> 12:53.175
I was bitten by a rattlesnake.

12:53.242 --> 12:54.744
All right.

12:54.810 --> 12:58.681
When there's company,
you sleep in there.
Is that right?

12:58.748 --> 13:00.683
That's right.

13:00.750 --> 13:02.117
You're not her husband?

13:02.184 --> 13:03.252
No, sir.

13:05.154 --> 13:07.357
Not for lack of asking.

13:07.423 --> 13:09.191
They your children?

13:09.258 --> 13:10.993
No.

13:11.060 --> 13:13.663
What happened
to their father?

13:15.130 --> 13:17.266
You don't know this?

13:21.170 --> 13:25.040
I can't say what all
happened between you two...

13:25.107 --> 13:26.642
but you ain't
welcome here, sir.

13:27.309 --> 13:28.911
[SIGHS]

13:29.912 --> 13:32.214
But she's a good Christian.

13:32.281 --> 13:33.449
Hm.

13:33.516 --> 13:36.318
She won't turn away
any man in need.

13:36.386 --> 13:39.522
Tomorrow, she'll give you
what doctoring she can...

13:39.589 --> 13:41.591
then you're on your way.

13:49.064 --> 13:51.401
There are some places where a
father would kill a young man

13:51.467 --> 13:54.937
for doing what you're doing,
you know that, don't you?

14:10.185 --> 14:11.787
[DOOR CLOSES]

14:43.619 --> 14:46.589
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

15:32.401 --> 15:35.771
If you have something to say,
say it.

15:35.838 --> 15:38.841
Are you really a Indian?

15:38.908 --> 15:41.711
Brake said you rode
with the Chiricahua.

15:41.777 --> 15:43.713
That's right.

15:43.779 --> 15:46.181
So that means
I'm part Indian, right?

15:46.248 --> 15:48.551
No.

15:48.618 --> 15:50.052
Not at all.

16:11.306 --> 16:12.975
You look stupid
trying to work

16:13.042 --> 16:15.444
in those fancy clothes,
you know.

16:15.511 --> 16:18.380
I am leaving here
as soon as I can.

16:18.447 --> 16:19.682
I'm moving to the city.

16:19.749 --> 16:21.416
But Grandpa's visiting.

16:21.483 --> 16:23.452
Did you see him?

16:23.519 --> 16:25.254
He's a savage.

16:25.320 --> 16:27.890
They're gut-eaters, you know.

16:31.627 --> 16:33.395
I was born into
the wrong family,

16:33.462 --> 16:35.765
I swear to God I was.

16:47.643 --> 16:48.878
[DOOR OPENS]

16:51.614 --> 16:52.648
I appreciate this.

16:52.715 --> 16:53.716
Take off your shirt.

16:53.783 --> 16:55.084
Magdalena--

16:55.150 --> 16:58.320
Don't call me that.
It's not my name.

17:08.130 --> 17:10.566
Where's it hurt?
Hurts when I breathe.

17:10.633 --> 17:12.300
Mostly around here.

17:23.545 --> 17:24.946
Yeah.

17:25.013 --> 17:28.150
Your muscles are torn
just under your ribs.

17:28.217 --> 17:31.120
You need to put
a cottonwood plaster to it.

17:34.456 --> 17:36.258
You'll live.

17:36.325 --> 17:40.195
I never thought you'd
turn out to be a healer.

17:40.262 --> 17:42.732
I remember you had
that yellow cat one time.

17:42.798 --> 17:45.334
You're crying because
a badger bit its tail off.

17:45.400 --> 17:46.869
Don't remember.
Your mother came running--

17:46.936 --> 17:49.972
Not in front of me.

17:50.039 --> 17:52.808
Because I remember my mother.

17:52.875 --> 17:57.012
My mother died
scrubbing a man's floor.

17:57.079 --> 17:59.148
And you killed her.

17:59.214 --> 18:01.884
Didn't shoot her or stab her,
but what you did...

18:04.219 --> 18:05.487
You broke her!

18:06.856 --> 18:09.925
And I remember my brother too.

18:09.992 --> 18:12.561
He lasted six years.

18:12.628 --> 18:15.097
I bet you never even
knew his name.

18:15.164 --> 18:17.366
And I remember praying hard
every night

18:17.432 --> 18:19.134
that you'd come home.

18:19.201 --> 18:21.136
But on the day I put him
in the ground

18:21.203 --> 18:23.605
I remember praying even harder
you were dead.

18:23.673 --> 18:29.144
So you don't want to reminisce
with me, that I promise you.

18:29.211 --> 18:32.414
I earned this money
in large part

18:32.481 --> 18:36.018
killing mountain lions
for ranchers like you.

18:36.085 --> 18:38.253
I want you to have it.

18:38.320 --> 18:40.756
If I were destitute
and drawing my last breath--

18:40.823 --> 18:42.124
This is good money.

18:42.191 --> 18:43.959
You take this money
for your children.

18:44.026 --> 18:45.294
No! You take it
for your funeral.
Magdalena...

18:46.862 --> 18:48.731
I've done my duty
as a Christian.

18:48.798 --> 18:50.199
You get the hell off my ranch!

18:50.265 --> 18:51.266
[EMILIANO SPEAKS SPANISH]

18:53.669 --> 18:55.137
[GUNSHOT]

18:56.839 --> 18:58.340
I'd stop now.

19:01.811 --> 19:03.278
[GUN COCKS]

19:04.714 --> 19:06.315
Maggie asked you to leave.

19:08.884 --> 19:11.653
I think it's time
you did so, sir.

19:15.925 --> 19:17.526
Right about now.

19:27.870 --> 19:31.340
[**]

19:43.552 --> 19:45.254
So long.

19:49.892 --> 19:52.061
Nice making your acquaintance.

20:05.407 --> 20:08.477
What's done is done, I guess.

20:16.886 --> 20:19.822
I know you would have
done different.

20:22.758 --> 20:26.295
I appreciate
your regard, Brake.

20:26.361 --> 20:27.963
I do.

20:48.851 --> 20:50.652
Well, night, then.

20:55.057 --> 20:57.793
Did they see you come in?

21:08.804 --> 21:10.973
We can't make a sound.

21:30.292 --> 21:32.794
Figure we can get them
all branded in a day?

21:32.862 --> 21:34.129
You want Dot to stay
for company?

21:34.196 --> 21:36.165
Brake, you said I could go.

21:36.231 --> 21:39.101
You promised.
Mama, you promised too.

21:39.168 --> 21:42.404
Oh, I'm fine.
He won't be coming back.

21:43.605 --> 21:46.075
This will help
the cramping.

21:49.211 --> 21:51.113
The calves are
a lot more important

21:51.180 --> 21:52.481
than hearing your own voice

21:52.547 --> 21:54.049
coming out of some machine,
you know?

21:54.116 --> 21:55.985
Well, I guess you never
had anything but this.

21:56.051 --> 21:57.519
So why should I?

22:02.357 --> 22:03.993
Come on, let's get going.

22:06.361 --> 22:09.064
You sure look frilly
to be working cattle.

22:10.599 --> 22:12.801
I'll keep an eye on them.

22:12.868 --> 22:14.303
Just be home before dark.

22:14.369 --> 22:16.238
All right.

22:16.305 --> 22:18.173
All right.

22:38.527 --> 22:40.129
[GOATS BLEATING]

22:43.365 --> 22:45.567
Easy now.

22:45.634 --> 22:47.469
That's right.

22:47.536 --> 22:50.205
[COWS MOOING]

23:32.814 --> 23:34.816
[BIRD CRIES]

23:39.354 --> 23:42.624
[**]

24:10.452 --> 24:13.422
[ROOSTER CROWS]

24:16.125 --> 24:18.327
[HORSE WHINNIES]

24:18.393 --> 24:20.862
[SADDLE JANGLING]

24:31.506 --> 24:33.608
Dot?

24:36.345 --> 24:37.646
Dot?

24:37.712 --> 24:39.114
[GLASS SHATTERING]

24:40.049 --> 24:41.916
Darling?

24:45.420 --> 24:47.722
Get! Get!

24:52.927 --> 24:54.996
Dot?

25:11.280 --> 25:14.583
[**]

25:35.304 --> 25:37.272
[HORSES SNORTING]

25:40.642 --> 25:43.378
[HORSE STARTLES, WHINNIES]

27:38.760 --> 27:39.828
Ah!

27:40.562 --> 27:42.764
No!

27:42.831 --> 27:45.200
No!

27:46.501 --> 27:48.337
[SCREAMING]

27:48.403 --> 27:49.904
[SOBBING]

28:00.815 --> 28:02.517
Dot!

28:08.457 --> 28:11.393
Oh, Lord. Darling.

28:11.460 --> 28:13.395
Mama, I'm cold.

28:13.462 --> 28:14.763
I'm here, darling.
Are you all right?

28:14.829 --> 28:19.334
I'm cold. I'm cold.

28:19.401 --> 28:21.270
Mama, I'm cold.

28:21.336 --> 28:23.171
Darling, where's Lilly?

28:24.806 --> 28:28.610
Emiliano...
Yeah, I know.

28:28.677 --> 28:30.745
Darling, where's Lilly?

28:30.812 --> 28:32.547
Emiliano and me...

28:34.616 --> 28:37.519
we was in the arroyo.

28:37.586 --> 28:42.291
We heard shots from where
Brake and Lilly was.

28:43.592 --> 28:45.794
He told me, "Stay down"...

28:45.860 --> 28:47.996
Emiliano did.

28:48.062 --> 28:51.966
"Don't move. Stay down."

28:52.033 --> 28:54.769
He went to see...

28:54.836 --> 28:58.006
but he didn't come back.

28:58.072 --> 29:01.810
I waited like he said,
but he didn't come back.

29:04.579 --> 29:07.181
Brake was screaming, Mama.

29:07.248 --> 29:10.785
He screamed so long
I wanted him to stop.

29:10.852 --> 29:12.621
I know. I know it.

29:12.687 --> 29:13.788
I know it.

29:13.855 --> 29:15.924
Then he did.

29:15.990 --> 29:19.093
Then someone rode away
with Lilly.

29:22.063 --> 29:25.033
I wanted him to stop!

29:25.099 --> 29:26.100
[SCREAMING AND SOBBING]

29:26.167 --> 29:28.637
I know it.
I know it.

29:28.703 --> 29:31.740
Darling, did you see who?

29:31.806 --> 29:33.308
Who took your sister?

29:35.043 --> 29:37.178
He wore a hood.

29:37.245 --> 29:39.113
He was Indian.

29:45.520 --> 29:49.023
[**]

30:19.087 --> 30:22.123
[ORGAN PLAYING]

30:22.190 --> 30:24.192
I'm sorry
for your loss, ma'am,

30:24.258 --> 30:26.661
but I'm afraid you got
the wrong fella in mind.

30:26.728 --> 30:28.630
I've had the man
you're describing in jail

30:28.697 --> 30:30.231
since last night.

30:30.298 --> 30:33.234
Sold himself a lion's hide
and got quite a drunk on.

30:33.301 --> 30:35.804
Unacceptable drunk.

30:35.870 --> 30:38.940
He did say he was staying out
by your place, though.

30:39.007 --> 30:41.710
There's been raids like this
on people here lately

30:41.776 --> 30:43.945
in Arizona and New Mexico.

30:44.012 --> 30:45.880
Some Apaches
jumped the reservation

30:45.947 --> 30:48.349
at San Carlos middle
of last month sometime.

30:48.417 --> 30:50.218
We've been getting
communications about them

30:50.284 --> 30:52.220
near every day.

30:53.688 --> 30:56.024
To Fort Bowie.

30:56.090 --> 30:57.926
From me.

30:59.360 --> 31:04.298
Possible your hostiles
attacked local ranch.

31:04.365 --> 31:08.236
Two dead,
one girl missing.

31:08.302 --> 31:10.439
Named...

31:10.505 --> 31:12.106
Lilly Gilkeson.

31:13.041 --> 31:15.477
Lilly Gilkeson.

31:15.544 --> 31:18.112
Stop.

31:18.179 --> 31:20.048
This takes just a moment.

31:20.114 --> 31:22.851
The device is truly a miracle.

31:24.819 --> 31:28.457
SALESMAN: And now you'll hear
your voice back
as clear as day.

31:28.523 --> 31:29.858
Ladies.

31:29.924 --> 31:32.561
WOMAN: My name's Louise Dewey.

31:32.627 --> 31:35.263
VOICE FROM GRAPHOPHONE:
My name's Louise Dewey.

31:38.933 --> 31:40.168
[CABLE CLICKING]

31:40.234 --> 31:45.339
To Sheriff Purdy...

31:45.406 --> 31:47.676
of Chloride.

31:47.742 --> 31:51.279
Believe hostiles...

31:51.345 --> 31:54.583
headed northwest...

31:54.649 --> 31:58.787
toward Colorado River.

31:58.853 --> 32:01.122
Fourth Cavalry...

32:01.189 --> 32:03.892
will pursue...

32:03.958 --> 32:07.662
in due course.

32:09.297 --> 32:11.700
Well, there you have it.

32:11.766 --> 32:17.405
I'll send the undertaker
out for the, uh...

32:17.472 --> 32:18.573
for the remains.

32:18.640 --> 32:22.544
You're not going after them?

32:22.611 --> 32:24.946
Not under the present
circumstances, ma'am, no.

32:25.013 --> 32:26.715
With the fair
being in town and all,

32:26.781 --> 32:28.349
I need all the men
I have right here.

32:28.416 --> 32:30.985
If you don't follow now,
their trail will get cold.

32:31.052 --> 32:32.821
The Army is handling
the situation.

32:32.887 --> 32:34.756
They have Apache scouts.

32:34.823 --> 32:36.257
Takes an Apache
to catch an Apache.

32:36.324 --> 32:39.127
If someone doesn't go now,
my daughter may be dead.

32:40.995 --> 32:45.333
Ma'am, I am elected to keep
vigil over this town of ours.

32:45.399 --> 32:49.738
Just one or two men, sir,
that's all I'm asking.

32:49.804 --> 32:52.841
Ma'am, I am sorry.

32:52.907 --> 32:55.744
Seth, I need a word with you.

32:57.111 --> 33:00.649
DOT: It was
the Indians did it.

33:00.715 --> 33:02.584
SALESMAN: Now, ladies,
I will not authorize

33:02.651 --> 33:05.319
fireworks until
a water wagon is here.

33:07.088 --> 33:09.991
SHERIFF: Ma'am, that's the
drunkard from last night.

33:10.058 --> 33:12.260
What would you like me
to do with him?

33:12.326 --> 33:15.830
Let him go.

33:15.897 --> 33:17.265
I don't care.

33:23.171 --> 33:25.306
[HORSE WHINNIES]

33:33.715 --> 33:35.049
Mama?

33:39.854 --> 33:41.122
Darling.

33:44.092 --> 33:45.560
[COUGHS]

33:45.627 --> 33:48.529
I, um, I want you to ride
over to the Handys'...

33:48.597 --> 33:49.931
No. No, I won't.

33:49.998 --> 33:51.633
and stay at their place
till I get back.

33:51.700 --> 33:53.167
I'm not gonna stay behind.

33:53.234 --> 33:56.638
I'll follow you as soon as
you're gone, you know I will.

33:56.705 --> 33:57.839
Darling--

33:57.906 --> 34:00.675
I'm not--
You can't leave me, Ma.

34:00.742 --> 34:04.012
I'm going with you, Mama,
please, I am.

34:04.078 --> 34:05.279
Now, you hear me, Dot--

34:05.346 --> 34:07.448
I'm not staying behind.

34:07.515 --> 34:10.652
Wherever you put me,
I'm coming after you, Ma.

34:10.719 --> 34:13.655
You know
I'm not gonna stay put.

34:13.722 --> 34:15.623
I swear to God,
I won't stay put.

34:15.690 --> 34:17.225
Ssh, ssh, ssh.

34:17.291 --> 34:18.592
Hush, hush.

34:20.795 --> 34:22.330
Hush, now. It's all right.

34:22.396 --> 34:24.498
[DOT SOBBING]

34:31.438 --> 34:32.907
Hush.

34:47.321 --> 34:50.123
The Army's headed
in the wrong direction.

34:51.760 --> 34:53.962
17 horse tracks.

34:54.027 --> 34:59.701
Three shod, one outrider,
two cavalry horses.

34:59.768 --> 35:04.172
Six horses were tied
together...

35:04.238 --> 35:05.573
carrying light loads.

35:05.640 --> 35:08.376
Probably young women,
children.

35:08.442 --> 35:10.511
And their captives...

35:10.578 --> 35:13.114
those are being led along...

35:13.181 --> 35:14.415
like packhorses.

35:14.482 --> 35:16.384
And they're headed south.

35:16.450 --> 35:18.887
Not north.

35:18.953 --> 35:21.222
Probably trying to make it
to the Mexican border.

35:25.059 --> 35:28.029
The Apaches sell
a lot of girls over there.

35:30.665 --> 35:32.266
Top dollar.

35:39.040 --> 35:40.274
Can you track them?

35:42.243 --> 35:44.946
You can track them.

35:45.013 --> 35:47.415
But if you catch them,
you'll wish you'd stayed
in that house.

35:47.481 --> 35:49.718
I don't wanna catch them.

35:49.784 --> 35:51.552
You just keep me
on their trail

35:51.619 --> 35:54.823
till I get the Army down
to Fort Selden to catch them.

36:01.095 --> 36:04.065
You wanted to give me money.

36:07.468 --> 36:08.937
Do this instead.

36:16.510 --> 36:18.212
[HORSE SNORTING]

36:18.279 --> 36:20.148
[SADDLE JANGLING]

36:36.731 --> 36:38.666
Taking this child out there
is awful foolish.

36:38.733 --> 36:41.803
I know my daughter.

36:41.870 --> 36:43.671
Leave her behind,
she'll just be following.

36:43.738 --> 36:45.974
No way to care
for a young girl.

36:46.040 --> 36:48.076
What would you know
about any of it?

36:50.578 --> 36:53.114
I'll be just fine, thank you.

37:00.688 --> 37:02.390
[HORSE WHINNIES]

37:11.032 --> 37:13.534
[COW MOOS]

37:17.238 --> 37:20.541
[**]

37:48.102 --> 37:50.771
[SNIFFLES]

37:50.839 --> 37:52.673
Come on, now.

38:10.524 --> 38:14.028
[**]

39:25.733 --> 39:27.535
MAN:
Pretty moon, Anne.

39:27.601 --> 39:30.504
Old Bob Hadley was supposed
to stop by tonight.

39:36.744 --> 39:38.479
God.

39:44.718 --> 39:47.521
[CHOPPING SOUNDS]

39:47.588 --> 39:50.491
Mama, I'm afraid in my room.

39:52.126 --> 39:54.428
It's just your fever
giving you bad dreams, honey.

39:54.495 --> 39:55.729
[BABY COUGHS]

39:55.796 --> 39:58.266
You want Mama
to sing you a song?

39:58.332 --> 40:02.736
* .FrÃ¨re Jacques
FrÃ¨re Jacques *

40:02.803 --> 40:05.573
* .Dourmez vous?
Dourmez vous? *

40:05.639 --> 40:07.875
* La la la la la

40:07.942 --> 40:10.811
[HUMMING]

40:38.339 --> 40:41.442
Your man didn't
keep his rifle very clean.

40:44.578 --> 40:46.114
Well, if he wanted
to marry you, though,

40:46.180 --> 40:48.216
I guess that's something.

40:50.084 --> 40:52.020
He's not all bad.

40:55.856 --> 40:57.158
Did you ever marry?

40:57.225 --> 40:59.427
Dot's father
was my husband.

40:59.493 --> 41:02.963
He built the ranch with me.

41:03.031 --> 41:06.434
The notion of it was better
than the doing, I guess.

41:08.969 --> 41:11.339
What about
the other one's father?

41:13.974 --> 41:17.078
Didn't get much
of a look at him.

41:17.145 --> 41:18.579
Maggie?

41:20.948 --> 41:23.484
What you're doing,
you're doing
for your own soul.

41:23.551 --> 41:27.355
Because what you've done,
you can't undo.

41:31.759 --> 41:33.394
[CAMERA POWDER POPS]

41:36.497 --> 41:38.599
You can all move now.

41:39.500 --> 41:41.969
[INDIANS CHATTERING]

41:49.877 --> 41:51.145
Sir, uh...

41:52.680 --> 41:56.284
Do you suppose it's safe
for me to be on my way now?

41:56.350 --> 41:58.619
Mister, I don't
suppose nothing.

41:58.686 --> 42:00.154
You're theirs now.

42:00.221 --> 42:02.190
They captured you.

42:03.957 --> 42:05.626
Could you help me, please?

42:07.895 --> 42:11.799
Go into the cave.
Bring picture-maker. Go!

42:19.140 --> 42:20.474
Take them.

42:20.541 --> 42:22.943
[BABY COUGHING]

42:26.147 --> 42:27.848
You're heartless.

42:30.551 --> 42:32.052
[BABY GAGGING]

42:32.120 --> 42:33.687
PHOTOGRAPHER:
I see you gentlemen

42:33.754 --> 42:36.524
are engaging in a little
frontier recreation out here.

42:36.590 --> 42:39.193
ISAAC: No, these girls
are going to market.

42:39.260 --> 42:41.995
We ain't supposed to sully
the merchandise.

42:47.801 --> 42:51.272
I can smell him from here.

42:52.473 --> 42:54.975
[MEN LAUGHING]

42:58.946 --> 43:00.548
I see you share a fondness

43:00.614 --> 43:03.651
for the photographic arts
like myself.

43:03.717 --> 43:07.521
Where did you find
this squashed penis?

43:11.425 --> 43:15.028
We captured him
as a gift for you.

43:15.095 --> 43:16.730
Sir, may I have the honor

43:16.797 --> 43:19.933
of posing you
with your captives, please?

43:21.369 --> 43:23.371
He wants to take your picture.

43:24.938 --> 43:26.907
Please, please.

43:34.415 --> 43:37.918
That's perfect. Now...

43:37.985 --> 43:39.086
very still.

43:39.153 --> 43:41.255
Help us. Help.

43:41.322 --> 43:43.457
Please help us.

43:51.599 --> 43:52.766
Look your best.

44:15.489 --> 44:16.790
Lord, protect us.

44:18.626 --> 44:20.494
Stay behind me.

45:00.868 --> 45:02.169
Indians.

45:02.236 --> 45:04.538
Yeah.

45:04.605 --> 45:06.240
But not the way
you're thinking.

45:09.277 --> 45:10.411
Is there time enough

45:10.478 --> 45:12.580
to give these men
a proper Christian burial?

45:12.646 --> 45:14.748
Dead's dead,
one way or the other.

45:14.815 --> 45:17.117
I asked if there was time.

45:24.124 --> 45:26.159
Yeah.

45:26.226 --> 45:27.628
There's time.

45:34.134 --> 45:36.870
[HORSE WHINNIES]

45:38.272 --> 45:39.740
Get in.

45:55.222 --> 45:58.592
You must be
the pride of your people.

45:58.659 --> 46:01.562
And you of yours.

46:01.629 --> 46:03.030
MAN:
Prepare to dismount!

46:05.098 --> 46:06.467
Dismount!

46:10.438 --> 46:14.041
SOLDIER: The two on the porch
have expired, lieutenant.

46:14.107 --> 46:16.310
Ask him why he murdered
those men in the yard.

46:16.377 --> 46:19.380
I didn't murder anybody.
They were dead
when I got here.

46:19.447 --> 46:21.214
What are you
doing in here?

46:21.281 --> 46:23.384
My granddaughter
was stolen two days ago.

46:23.451 --> 46:25.252
I trailed her to this place.

46:27.588 --> 46:29.323
What's her name?

46:30.724 --> 46:32.125
Uh...

46:32.192 --> 46:35.195
You don't know your
granddaughter's name?

46:35.262 --> 46:37.765
Well,
her sister's name is Dot.

46:37.831 --> 46:41.469
We found two horses with
a bunch of women's property
in them.

46:45.305 --> 46:46.474
Hang him.

46:56.249 --> 46:57.818
SOLDIER: Other side!

46:57.885 --> 46:59.286
There he goes!

47:12.232 --> 47:13.501
I didn't kill anyone!

47:16.370 --> 47:18.171
I said, I didn't kill anyone!

47:18.238 --> 47:19.773
Come out and show your hands!

47:19.840 --> 47:22.242
I am looking
for my granddaughter!

47:22.309 --> 47:23.477
Then you tell me
her damn name!

47:26.547 --> 47:27.781
I don't know her damn name!

47:27.848 --> 47:29.750
Lilly!

47:32.986 --> 47:34.287
Lilly Gilkeson.

47:34.354 --> 47:36.924
You know this Indian?

47:36.990 --> 47:38.058
He's no Indian.

47:38.125 --> 47:39.493
Damn well looks Indian to me.

47:40.961 --> 47:42.596
No, he's a...

47:46.166 --> 47:47.535
That's my father.

47:49.403 --> 47:53.607
I've been hoping
we'd find you, sir.
We need your help.

47:55.342 --> 47:58.646
We tracked my daughter
south from Chloride.

47:58.712 --> 48:01.615
They're heading toward Mexico.

48:01.682 --> 48:03.283
Near as we can figure

48:03.350 --> 48:05.686
they've hit six or seven
homesteads so far,

48:05.753 --> 48:06.987
including this one.

48:07.054 --> 48:08.656
Sir, Army should've
killed those heathens

48:08.722 --> 48:09.923
when they had the chance.

48:09.990 --> 48:12.760
They are Army, ma'am.
Deserters.

48:12.826 --> 48:15.629
Why, I thought
they were Apache.

48:15.696 --> 48:17.364
Apache scouts.

48:17.431 --> 48:19.633
Formerly on
Uncle Sam's payroll.

48:19.700 --> 48:21.301
Like Happy Jim here.

48:21.368 --> 48:23.036
We use them to hunt down
other Apaches.

48:23.103 --> 48:26.640
These Indians
were American soldiers?

48:26.707 --> 48:31.078
Then a couple of months ago,
some of them turned

48:31.144 --> 48:32.480
shot some white officers

48:32.546 --> 48:35.248
and jumped the reservation
in San Carlos.

48:35.315 --> 48:39.152
The 4th Cavalry started
all this by hanging
their chief.

48:41.021 --> 48:42.856
Don't know what
they were thinking.

48:42.923 --> 48:44.992
What makes you think
they were thinking?

48:48.562 --> 48:51.331
This whole territory's
gone topsy-turvy.

48:51.398 --> 48:52.900
You got Indians
running with whites,

48:52.966 --> 48:55.002
whites running with Indians.

48:56.436 --> 48:58.271
SOLDIER:
Get those prisoners moving!

48:58.338 --> 49:01.609
Come on, squaw man.
Get on the way here.

49:06.947 --> 49:08.281
Happy Jim.

49:12.419 --> 49:16.423
You think because you're
wearing that coat

49:16.490 --> 49:22.462
they won't put you on
the prison train to Florida
with chains on your legs?

49:23.564 --> 49:26.266
I don't know of Florida.

49:27.801 --> 49:33.206
It's a real swell shit-hole
of a swamp.

49:33.273 --> 49:35.175
You'll see.

49:35.242 --> 49:38.311
White man, you don't look like
someone who gives good advice.

49:38.378 --> 49:39.412
[SPITS]

49:42.082 --> 49:43.617
Break it up!

49:43.684 --> 49:47.187
What's going on here?
I said, break it up.

49:49.590 --> 49:50.791
I found it first,
lieutenant.

49:50.858 --> 49:52.125
Lying bastard!

49:54.227 --> 49:56.396
LIEUTENANT: Looks like
God intended you two to share.

49:58.231 --> 50:00.367
Any man found looting...

50:00.433 --> 50:01.835
will have the value
of their property

50:01.902 --> 50:04.137
deducted from his pay.

50:10.678 --> 50:14.081
They're enlisted men.

50:14.147 --> 50:15.215
LIEUTENANT:
Post two men over there.

50:15.282 --> 50:18.151
I'm going to camp
down by the river.

50:18.218 --> 50:20.187
If I stay here long,
I might misbehave.

50:20.253 --> 50:21.589
--right over there.

50:21.655 --> 50:24.091
Somebody might have to
kill me.

50:33.300 --> 50:34.935
Lieutenant?

50:36.436 --> 50:38.639
I imagine you plan
to ride first thing.

50:38.706 --> 50:40.473
Would it be all right
if my daughter and I

50:40.540 --> 50:42.475
rode along with you?

50:42.542 --> 50:44.578
Naturally,
I'm quite concerned.

50:44.645 --> 50:48.515
Ma'am,
capturing those renegades is
the Army's highest priority.

50:48.582 --> 50:49.983
Yes, of course.

50:50.050 --> 50:51.418
Butcher a couple of those
goats for supper!

50:51.484 --> 50:52.786
And I'm grateful.

50:52.853 --> 50:54.988
But that's the assignment
of the 4th.

50:56.790 --> 50:59.793
But the 4th is going
in the wrong direction.

50:59.860 --> 51:01.929
I assure you,
they'll be redirected

51:01.995 --> 51:03.631
as soon as we reach
Fort Stanton.

51:03.697 --> 51:05.132
Stanton's three days away,
lieutenant.

51:05.198 --> 51:06.900
My daughter will be
in Mexico by then.

51:06.967 --> 51:10.037
Ma'am, I grieve for your
situation, I truly do.

51:10.103 --> 51:12.272
But my assignment is to return
these hostiles in my capture

51:12.339 --> 51:17.310
to Stanton for their prompt
and immediate deportation.

51:53.981 --> 51:55.148
You like fish?

51:55.215 --> 51:57.718
MAGGIE:
Go water the horses.

51:57.785 --> 52:00.220
I watered them back at the--
I'm not asking.

52:03.056 --> 52:05.425
Don't make them
too raw, please.

52:06.393 --> 52:08.461
Very well, ma'am.

52:16.169 --> 52:20.107
Lilly, she's...

52:20.173 --> 52:21.809
not the same as Dot.

52:22.876 --> 52:25.178
She's not strong.

52:25.245 --> 52:28.281
She gets hurt so easy.

52:34.021 --> 52:35.588
Sage?

52:35.655 --> 52:39.026
What?
For the fish.

52:39.092 --> 52:41.094
Look, I know I only
asked you to get us

52:41.161 --> 52:42.730
as far as the the Army--

52:42.796 --> 52:46.566
I asked you if you wanted
some sage put on your fish.

52:51.371 --> 52:54.407
Yeah. All right.

52:55.208 --> 52:56.476
None for Dot.

53:02.850 --> 53:04.918
We'll ride at first light
in the morning.

53:07.654 --> 53:08.889
If we can catch up to them,

53:08.956 --> 53:10.991
I might have enough money
to buy her back.

53:16.596 --> 53:19.366
If they make it to Mexico...

53:19.432 --> 53:21.468
your child is lost.

53:30.811 --> 53:34.314
Hey, that stuff will make you
sick, but I like it.

53:58.638 --> 54:00.841
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

54:00.908 --> 54:02.142
No, no, no, no. Whoa.

54:02.209 --> 54:04.677
That flash behind her head
bother you? It's just--

54:04.744 --> 54:06.113
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

54:07.614 --> 54:11.384
There's no magic.
It's an optical defect.
A flaw.

54:11.451 --> 54:12.786
A flaw. Flaw.

54:14.021 --> 54:15.022
Wait, wait. Hey, wait.

54:16.356 --> 54:18.725
Look at these.
Look at these. See?

54:18.792 --> 54:20.994
I know where all
the prettiest girls live,

54:21.061 --> 54:22.529
from Arizona to Texas.

54:22.595 --> 54:24.164
You pick the ones you want,

54:24.231 --> 54:26.333
and
I'll take you right to them.
Right to their door! Look!

54:26.399 --> 54:27.600
All the pretty girls, see?

54:27.667 --> 54:30.770
All of them!
I'll take you-- Look!

54:39.146 --> 54:41.214
Take your bad luck to your
grave.

54:41.281 --> 54:42.615
What was that?

54:46.820 --> 54:48.755
What did you just do?

54:50.157 --> 54:51.424
ISAAC:
I'll get it done.

54:53.093 --> 54:55.795
Uh, who of you
can skin a deer?

54:58.598 --> 55:02.169
Hey! Who of you can skin
a deer?

55:02.235 --> 55:05.438
Me. I can.

55:12.479 --> 55:14.081
All right. Gotta gut her.

55:50.150 --> 55:51.651
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

55:51.718 --> 55:53.954
PHOTOGRAPHER:
I can't see.

55:54.021 --> 55:55.522
What is happening to me?

55:57.524 --> 56:00.693
Somebody tell me.
What is happening?

56:00.760 --> 56:05.132
I can't see.
I can't see. Please!

56:06.499 --> 56:08.168
I can't-- Wh--

56:10.537 --> 56:11.972
[YELLING]

56:47.507 --> 56:51.711
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

56:54.614 --> 56:56.016
Hey, where's clubfoot going?

56:56.083 --> 56:58.651
I thought we was dropping
back down into Mexico.

56:58.718 --> 57:00.353
Seven's an unlucky number
for him.

57:00.420 --> 57:04.291
He wants eight girls.
We go now.

57:04.357 --> 57:05.925
Shit!

57:08.428 --> 57:09.529
Here.

57:12.532 --> 57:14.034
Fill the packs with meat.

57:15.602 --> 57:19.772
I gotta take Sally. No,
I gotta take my little girl.

57:19.839 --> 57:23.843
No! She just needs water.
She's fine.

57:23.910 --> 57:25.912
Shut up.
She's dead now, mama.

57:25.979 --> 57:27.380
She's my baby.
Shut up.

57:27.447 --> 57:29.782
No!

57:29.849 --> 57:31.918
[YELLING IN APACHE]

57:36.656 --> 57:38.825
No! No! No!

57:39.826 --> 57:41.494
No, no, no, no.

57:41.561 --> 57:43.163
No!

57:44.764 --> 57:46.699
Get up!

57:46.766 --> 57:49.169
Get up!

57:49.236 --> 57:50.803
Get up!

57:51.838 --> 57:53.840
Trying to make a fool of me.

57:56.843 --> 57:59.379
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

57:59.446 --> 58:01.381
It's gonna be all right.

58:17.364 --> 58:20.700
I think my feet
grew two sizes today.

58:23.270 --> 58:24.971
Try these.

58:32.579 --> 58:34.414
They're beautiful.

58:34.481 --> 58:36.015
They were my wife's.

58:37.850 --> 58:39.018
My grandmother?

58:43.923 --> 58:45.525
No.

59:30.803 --> 59:33.173
[DOT SCREAMS]

59:33.240 --> 59:34.807
DOT: Mama!

59:36.343 --> 59:37.777
Mama!
MAGGIE: Dot?

59:40.413 --> 59:42.482
You all right?

59:42.549 --> 59:45.051
You get bit?
Did those snakes bite you?

59:45.118 --> 59:46.719
No.

59:46.786 --> 59:48.821
Mama, a dead man's in there.

59:49.956 --> 59:52.259
Don't worry about that child.

59:54.060 --> 59:55.762
Go on now.

01:00:00.066 --> 01:00:01.401
Mama, look at his eyes.

01:00:06.739 --> 01:00:08.141
DOT: What happened to him?

01:00:08.208 --> 01:00:10.143
MAGGIE: He lost control
of his wagon.

01:00:10.210 --> 01:00:11.578
Maybe he had a heart seizure.

01:00:11.644 --> 01:00:13.513
He didn't have
a heart seizure.

01:00:13.580 --> 01:00:14.814
His heart's in that hole.

01:00:39.706 --> 01:00:41.274
What's behind her head?

01:00:44.244 --> 01:00:46.045
Some people would think
it's a sign.

01:00:46.112 --> 01:00:47.647
A good sign or bad sign?

01:00:47.714 --> 01:00:50.082
It wasn't a very good sign for
that fella. Come here, child.

01:00:53.420 --> 01:00:54.454
What are you doing?

01:00:54.521 --> 01:00:56.155
These are for protection.

01:00:56.223 --> 01:00:58.991
The man who did this
is a brujo.

01:00:59.058 --> 01:01:01.594
A what?
It's a witch.

01:01:01.661 --> 01:01:03.230
You need to wear one too.

01:01:03.296 --> 01:01:05.131
You can believe in
your witchcraft

01:01:05.198 --> 01:01:06.933
and your impiety all you want.

01:01:06.999 --> 01:01:09.336
I believe in
what I've seen, girl.

01:01:09.402 --> 01:01:12.405
Snakes belong on the ground.
This one hangs them
in the air.

01:01:12.472 --> 01:01:13.640
A man's heart holds
his spirit.

01:01:13.706 --> 01:01:15.942
This one digs it out of his
body, bleeds it out

01:01:16.008 --> 01:01:18.010
and throws it in the dirt.
No. Don't you start this.

01:01:18.077 --> 01:01:20.413
I know a brujo strong enough
to put an arrow in you

01:01:20.480 --> 01:01:22.148
from one mile away.

01:01:22.215 --> 01:01:25.084
I know a brujo who laid
his hand on a child one time.
One time.

01:01:25.151 --> 01:01:26.786
The child cramped up,
fell down

01:01:26.853 --> 01:01:28.488
and spit up white bees
till she died.

01:01:28.555 --> 01:01:30.557
You stop this, you hear me?
You're scaring her.

01:01:30.623 --> 01:01:32.425
She needs to be scared
and so do you.

01:01:32.492 --> 01:01:35.528
Mama, please. Please.

01:01:43.736 --> 01:01:45.538
Just on her.

01:02:20.206 --> 01:02:23.109
[THUNDER ROLLS]

01:02:23.175 --> 01:02:26.212
We gotta get through
that canyon before
the storm hits.

01:02:26.279 --> 01:02:27.880
You go on and I'll follow.

01:02:35.588 --> 01:02:38.525
Hey, give me some of
the medical stuff they stole,
the laudanum.

01:02:38.591 --> 01:02:40.593
MAN:
You like that stuff.

01:02:43.330 --> 01:02:46.333
ISAAC: You know,
I drink enough of this stuff,
I swear...

01:02:46.399 --> 01:02:47.834
you start to look good to me.

01:02:47.900 --> 01:02:48.968
Hey.

01:02:49.035 --> 01:02:50.269
[LAUGHING]

01:02:50.337 --> 01:02:51.971
MAN: They give this
to my grandma

01:02:52.038 --> 01:02:53.306
when she was fixing to croak.

01:03:27.907 --> 01:03:30.377
[DOT SCREAMING]

01:03:30.443 --> 01:03:31.611
Mama!

01:03:32.845 --> 01:03:34.814
Mama!

01:03:36.082 --> 01:03:38.585
I'll get her!

01:03:38.651 --> 01:03:40.687
Catch those horses and
take them to higher ground!

01:03:40.753 --> 01:03:42.622
I've got her!

01:03:57.670 --> 01:03:59.806
Dot, you hold on to me!

01:03:59.872 --> 01:04:01.374
[DOT SCREAMS]

01:04:02.642 --> 01:04:04.110
[DOT COUGHING]

01:04:25.998 --> 01:04:27.800
DOT: My foot's caught!

01:04:44.016 --> 01:04:46.719
Hold your breath! Right now!

01:05:41.073 --> 01:05:42.241
Gotta piss.

01:06:11.704 --> 01:06:13.272
Sit up. Sshh!

01:06:17.443 --> 01:06:19.478
I can get us out of here.

01:06:20.713 --> 01:06:23.449
Do you hear that?
You mustn't speak.

01:06:23.516 --> 01:06:26.218
My baby's calling me.

01:06:26.285 --> 01:06:29.421
No. I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

01:06:29.488 --> 01:06:32.659
Your baby's passed on.

01:06:32.725 --> 01:06:34.193
No.

01:06:34.260 --> 01:06:36.462
That's just how she sleeps.

01:06:36.529 --> 01:06:39.398
There's nothing you can do,
so please just--

01:06:46.472 --> 01:06:49.441
There, there. My baby.

01:06:51.043 --> 01:06:52.645
[SNORING]

01:07:00.519 --> 01:07:03.923
Here. Watch out while
I get the horses.

01:07:09.261 --> 01:07:12.398
Hey, I'm just going to get
those berries I promised you.

01:07:12.464 --> 01:07:14.233
Don't wander off.

01:07:23.309 --> 01:07:25.244
Lord, forgive me.

01:07:44.363 --> 01:07:46.999
[LILLY SCREAMS]

01:07:47.767 --> 01:07:49.068
Stop squirming.

01:07:51.570 --> 01:07:54.306
Goddamn you! Give her to me.

01:07:54.373 --> 01:07:56.075
Get up!
No!

01:07:56.142 --> 01:07:58.344
I got her.
No!

01:07:58.410 --> 01:08:01.147
Tie her legs!
Shut up!

01:08:01.213 --> 01:08:02.514
Shut up!

01:08:02.581 --> 01:08:04.684
Why?

01:08:06.118 --> 01:08:08.020
Now we're gonna be
back to seven,

01:08:08.087 --> 01:08:09.822
and seven's an unlucky number.

01:08:11.290 --> 01:08:13.492
Whore! Stop!

01:08:29.742 --> 01:08:31.143
Thank you.

01:08:33.345 --> 01:08:35.447
Crawl.

01:08:35.514 --> 01:08:38.584
You're better than them,
but you're not better than me.

01:08:59.872 --> 01:09:02.274
Can she have the moccasins
now?

01:09:08.848 --> 01:09:10.349
Yeah.

01:09:14.754 --> 01:09:16.388
Can I just--?

01:09:20.192 --> 01:09:22.428
I'm glad you were here.

01:09:31.170 --> 01:09:32.971
I was bitten
by a rattlesnake.

01:09:35.241 --> 01:09:36.809
What?

01:09:36.876 --> 01:09:40.078
A good shaman gave me
two amulets.

01:09:42.782 --> 01:09:46.518
Told me not to eat
rabbit meat for a year...

01:09:46.585 --> 01:09:50.055
to say my prayers every
morning...

01:09:50.122 --> 01:09:52.992
take care of my family,
and I might get well.

01:09:56.996 --> 01:09:59.565
You're telling me
the only reason you came back

01:09:59.631 --> 01:10:02.601
was because you were following
the say-so of some...

01:10:02.668 --> 01:10:04.937
medicine man.
Is that right?

01:10:05.004 --> 01:10:09.275
Yes. Absolutely. A rattlesnake
can make your soul...

01:10:12.344 --> 01:10:14.280
very sick.

01:10:16.849 --> 01:10:19.551
That's likely not
what you want to hear.

01:10:19.618 --> 01:10:21.754
But it is the truth.

01:10:54.086 --> 01:11:02.728
We have eight girls.
Now, we can go.

01:11:02.795 --> 01:11:07.533
No. This one ran,
let the mother kill herself.

01:11:22.982 --> 01:11:26.518
Go on. Hit me.

01:11:26.585 --> 01:11:28.821
You won't fetch as many pesos
with my face all swollen,

01:11:28.888 --> 01:11:29.922
and you know it.

01:11:41.433 --> 01:11:46.973
This is what the rest
of your life will taste like.

01:11:54.113 --> 01:11:56.215
Keep still.

01:12:24.643 --> 01:12:26.078
That them?

01:12:31.750 --> 01:12:35.054
[**]

01:12:49.868 --> 01:12:52.004
Once they clear those trees,
they'll be riding in line

01:12:52.071 --> 01:12:53.672
along that river.

01:12:53.739 --> 01:12:55.574
I'll shoot the front horse.

01:12:55.641 --> 01:12:59.378
You shoot a horse
in the middle.
We're lucky, they'll scatter.

01:12:59.445 --> 01:13:01.013
Thought we were
gonna buy her back.

01:13:01.080 --> 01:13:02.248
The more of them we kill

01:13:02.314 --> 01:13:04.283
the easier they'll be
to reason with.

01:13:06.552 --> 01:13:10.189
Maybe
she'll get clear and save us
the trouble altogether.

01:13:11.690 --> 01:13:14.193
Dot, you keep shooting.
Try to hit a horse.

01:13:35.747 --> 01:13:36.949
[GUN COCKS]

01:13:47.693 --> 01:13:50.762
Mother of Jesus...

01:13:50.829 --> 01:13:53.265
you watched your child suffer.

01:13:53.332 --> 01:13:58.937
Give me strength.
Stop my hands from trembling.

01:14:06.645 --> 01:14:08.014
Let them come on.

01:14:28.567 --> 01:14:31.970
Not yet. Not yet.

01:14:34.806 --> 01:14:39.145
Let them come.
Let them come.

01:14:44.816 --> 01:14:46.752
On my call,
pick a horse in the middle

01:14:46.818 --> 01:14:48.420
and shoot him in the neck.

01:15:14.446 --> 01:15:16.548
I can't see Lilly.

01:15:16.615 --> 01:15:18.250
Dot!

01:15:20.252 --> 01:15:22.020
[CHIDIN COMMANDING IN APACHE]

01:15:25.624 --> 01:15:28.227
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

01:15:30.196 --> 01:15:31.330
Take everything.

01:16:15.674 --> 01:16:18.177
[GUNSHOTS]

01:17:07.293 --> 01:17:08.427
[GUN COCKS]

01:17:09.795 --> 01:17:11.029
They're Chiricahua.

01:17:17.969 --> 01:17:21.139
Kayitah, where did you
steal that horse?

01:17:21.207 --> 01:17:27.546
Chaa-duu-ba-its-iidan?
Hasn't someone killed you yet?

01:17:27.613 --> 01:17:32.150
You still owe me
three lion hides, you know.

01:17:32.218 --> 01:17:34.152
I lived with him
and his family for a time.

01:17:34.220 --> 01:17:36.588
Good. That's good, isn't it?

01:17:36.655 --> 01:17:38.857
Name's Kayitah.

01:17:38.924 --> 01:17:40.526
Think the other one's his son.

01:17:53.239 --> 01:17:59.911
Forget the hides. Give us
your horses and your guns
and we'll call it even.

01:18:02.281 --> 01:18:03.482
They want our horses and guns.

01:18:03.549 --> 01:18:07.185
I am not giving over
my horses.

01:18:07.253 --> 01:18:10.422
You understand?
You'll have to kill me first.

01:18:12.090 --> 01:18:13.625
You tell him what I said.

01:18:14.693 --> 01:18:17.496
Now look. You pissed her off.

01:18:19.765 --> 01:18:24.936
How can you tell? You people
look pissed off all the time.

01:18:29.174 --> 01:18:31.577
You tell them
to get on their way.

01:18:31.643 --> 01:18:34.913
Even better, you tell them
we want their guns
and ammunition.

01:18:35.914 --> 01:18:38.183
Go on. You tell him.

01:18:38.250 --> 01:18:43.255
The men you just killed
were trying to kill us too.

01:18:46.492 --> 01:18:51.530
The witch stole
my son's future.

01:18:51.597 --> 01:18:55.133
His bride was taken
a week ago.

01:18:55.200 --> 01:18:59.671
He stole my granddaughter too.
We can help each other.

01:19:00.672 --> 01:19:03.875
And she's a healer.

01:19:36.708 --> 01:19:39.345
Ain't no undergarments
or nothing.

01:20:02.334 --> 01:20:04.069
Dot, bring me my bag.

01:20:16.348 --> 01:20:18.684
Go outside, sweetheart.

01:20:18.750 --> 01:20:22.654
You don't know what diseases
these people have.

01:20:40.972 --> 01:20:45.711
I don't usually operate
on Indians.

01:20:45.777 --> 01:20:48.046
They have green blood and
a pinecone in their chest

01:20:48.113 --> 01:20:49.615
instead of a heart.

01:20:50.716 --> 01:20:53.251
Just give me that mescal.

01:21:01.627 --> 01:21:04.062
All right. It'll hurt.

01:21:05.497 --> 01:21:06.798
Ssh, ssh, ssh.

01:21:26.552 --> 01:21:29.320
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

01:21:43.635 --> 01:21:52.143
Do you still go up north
and fool around with
that fat Zuni girl?

01:21:54.446 --> 01:21:56.782
Don't lie.

01:21:56.848 --> 01:22:00.852
No. She started
to like me too much.

01:22:16.201 --> 01:22:17.636
He told me...

01:22:17.703 --> 01:22:22.608
this brujo's mother
was raped by a witch.

01:22:22.674 --> 01:22:25.877
Came out of her womb two years
later with
a full set of teeth.

01:22:25.944 --> 01:22:28.814
I'm not feeling
too good myself.

01:22:51.169 --> 01:22:54.205
[KAYITAH SINGING SOFTLY]

01:23:03.114 --> 01:23:06.952
Don't sit too close, darling.
I'm not feeling too good.

01:23:10.856 --> 01:23:14.359
It's so cold.
It's not that cold, Ma.

01:23:16.728 --> 01:23:20.666
[SPEAKING SOFTLY]

01:23:23.234 --> 01:23:25.003
Hablas EspaÃ±ol?

01:23:29.340 --> 01:23:31.342
You knew my father?

01:23:33.745 --> 01:23:34.880
SÃ­.

01:23:36.948 --> 01:23:39.150
What do you remember
about him?

01:23:39.217 --> 01:23:45.591
We called him
Chaa-duu-ba-its-iidan.

01:23:48.193 --> 01:23:51.229
He was a good hunter.

01:23:51.296 --> 01:23:54.365
Yeah. He was.

01:23:55.801 --> 01:23:59.571
He married Laatsine.
His Chiricahua wife.

01:24:01.039 --> 01:24:03.775
Was she beautiful?

01:24:03.842 --> 01:24:05.510
No.

01:24:07.378 --> 01:24:11.650
She was cross-eyed.

01:24:13.384 --> 01:24:21.727
He was living with the Navajo
when she died of smallpox.

01:24:22.694 --> 01:24:27.398
She died... I didn't realize.

01:24:27.465 --> 01:24:32.337
Moved around a lot.
Never still,
Chaa-duu-ba-its-iidan.

01:24:32.403 --> 01:24:37.142
Moving spirits
don't make happy men.

01:24:37.208 --> 01:24:41.780
Did he love her?
His Chiricahua wife?

01:24:41.847 --> 01:24:46.017
He loved all of them.
For a time.

01:25:08.373 --> 01:25:09.775
Hello.

01:25:10.976 --> 01:25:12.143
What are you doing?

01:25:15.380 --> 01:25:18.616
I'm dreaming of what's
gonna happen tomorrow.

01:25:18.684 --> 01:25:20.251
Can I dream on it too?

01:25:21.386 --> 01:25:22.854
I don't know. Can you?

01:25:39.905 --> 01:25:41.539
Can't.

01:25:44.409 --> 01:25:47.846
Mom's talking
in her sleep again.

01:25:47.913 --> 01:25:51.616
Sometimes at home,
she talks so loud we have
to wake her up.

01:25:53.218 --> 01:25:55.120
Sometimes she cries.

01:25:55.186 --> 01:25:58.023
Other times, she sounds like
somebody's hurting her.

01:25:58.089 --> 01:26:00.525
And all the next day,
she looks at Lilly funny.

01:26:02.193 --> 01:26:06.131
Me and Lilly notice,
even though Mama doesn't,
I don't think.

01:26:09.634 --> 01:26:10.869
What happened to her?

01:26:10.936 --> 01:26:13.338
I don't know,
and I wouldn't ask.

01:26:17.542 --> 01:26:21.246
I think when she was young,
she was, um...

01:26:23.348 --> 01:26:25.616
treated with cruelty.

01:26:28.920 --> 01:26:31.156
She was alone in the world
at that time.

01:26:32.623 --> 01:26:34.192
You wish you'd been there?

01:26:37.662 --> 01:26:38.930
I don't wish.

01:26:40.365 --> 01:26:42.834
[GROANING]

01:26:44.002 --> 01:26:45.804
Mama.

01:26:57.148 --> 01:26:58.716
Ma, wake up,
you're having a bad--

01:26:58.784 --> 01:27:00.351
Don't touch her.

01:27:10.361 --> 01:27:13.431
[CHIDIN CHANTING IN APACHE]

01:27:20.872 --> 01:27:23.074
[MAGGIE MUTTERING]

01:27:37.588 --> 01:27:41.492
[CHIDIN CONTINUES CHANTING]

01:27:48.066 --> 01:27:50.701
The Brujo
has put a curse on her.

01:27:51.769 --> 01:27:53.972
I will gather some ghost bush.

01:27:59.277 --> 01:28:01.146
Go get your mother's Bible.

01:28:01.212 --> 01:28:03.548
Is it bees?
Go on.

01:28:06.517 --> 01:28:09.020
What did you leave
behind at that camp?

01:28:09.087 --> 01:28:13.658
Today. This day,
what did you leave behind?

01:28:13.724 --> 01:28:15.827
I don't... I don't know.

01:28:37.448 --> 01:28:40.151
Help me again to heal.

01:28:55.833 --> 01:29:01.439
Keep all evil away from here.

01:29:22.093 --> 01:29:25.863
Mama. Don't let him, Mama.

01:29:39.911 --> 01:29:42.780
[CHANTING]

01:29:47.818 --> 01:29:50.021
[CHANTING]

01:29:54.192 --> 01:29:56.394
[CHANTING]

01:29:59.197 --> 01:30:02.833
"Abraham begat Isaac,
and Isaac begat Jacob.

01:30:02.900 --> 01:30:05.937
"And Jacob begat Judas
and his brethren.

01:30:06.004 --> 01:30:09.207
"And Judas begat Phares
and Zara of Thamar.

01:30:09.274 --> 01:30:12.243
"And Phares begat Esrom,
and Esrom begat Aram.

01:30:12.310 --> 01:30:15.981
"And Aram begat Aminadab,
and Aminadab begat Naasson.

01:30:16.047 --> 01:30:20.285
"And Naasson begat Salmon,
and Salmon begat Booz
of Rachab.

01:30:20.351 --> 01:30:23.154
"And Booz begat Obed of Ruth,
and Obed begat Jesse.

01:30:23.221 --> 01:30:24.956
"And Jesse begat
David the king,

01:30:25.023 --> 01:30:26.791
"and David the king begat
Solomon,

01:30:26.857 --> 01:30:29.360
"of her that had been
the wife of Urias.

01:30:29.427 --> 01:30:32.763
"And Solomon begat Roboam,
and Roboam begat Abia.

01:30:32.830 --> 01:30:36.701
"And Abia begat Asa,
and Asa begat Josaphat.

01:30:36.767 --> 01:30:40.605
"Josaphat begat Joram,
and Joram begat Ozias.

01:30:40.671 --> 01:30:43.841
"And Ozias begat Joatham,
and Joatham begat Achaz.

01:30:43.908 --> 01:30:47.312
"And Achaz begat Ezekias,
and Ezekias begat Manasses.

01:30:47.378 --> 01:30:50.715
"And Manasses begat Amon,
and Amon begat Josias.

01:30:50.781 --> 01:30:53.284
And Josias begat Jechonias
and his brethren."

01:31:08.733 --> 01:31:10.268
[RESUMES CHANTING]

01:31:30.188 --> 01:31:32.557
-Let's attack them.
-We don't have a chance.

01:31:32.623 --> 01:31:35.260
Still, we must try.

01:31:35.326 --> 01:31:39.364
Father, I can fight too.

01:31:39.430 --> 01:31:41.132
No.

01:31:41.199 --> 01:31:42.567
You stay here.

01:31:45.403 --> 01:31:47.105
Morning.

01:31:48.005 --> 01:31:49.274
Good morning.

01:31:49.340 --> 01:31:52.243
Reckon I drank
from the wrong bottle.

01:31:52.310 --> 01:31:54.312
Wrong as can be.

01:31:58.449 --> 01:31:59.450
Here.

01:31:59.517 --> 01:32:02.453
You need to keep that on.

01:32:02.520 --> 01:32:05.256
You know, Dot was wearing hers
when she almost drowned.

01:32:05.323 --> 01:32:07.258
Yes.

01:32:07.325 --> 01:32:09.260
Almost.

01:32:12.163 --> 01:32:13.531
After we attacked them,

01:32:13.598 --> 01:32:15.533
you reckon we can still
buy them back?

01:32:15.600 --> 01:32:19.003
I don't know.
Money's always money.

01:32:19.070 --> 01:32:20.871
But we don't have enough
to buy them all, though.

01:32:20.938 --> 01:32:23.708
Two or three at the most.

01:32:23.774 --> 01:32:25.276
You get Lilly.

01:32:27.545 --> 01:32:32.950
And get the, uh,
the Indian girl...

01:32:33.017 --> 01:32:34.885
and...

01:32:34.952 --> 01:32:37.288
whoever else you can.

01:32:38.989 --> 01:32:41.092
Sorry for the rest.

01:32:50.768 --> 01:32:53.238
I'll see you again.

01:32:55.573 --> 01:32:57.842
Should be back by dark.

01:32:57.908 --> 01:33:00.211
If we're not,
leave at daylight tomorrow.

01:33:01.179 --> 01:33:02.613
That means go home.

01:33:02.680 --> 01:33:06.217
You and Dot.

01:33:06.284 --> 01:33:07.652
You understand?

01:33:13.591 --> 01:33:16.227
You tell me yes,
or I'm not going.

01:33:17.728 --> 01:33:19.597
I understand.

01:33:27.138 --> 01:33:28.506
Kayitah...

01:33:36.947 --> 01:33:39.049
Give this to my daughter.

01:33:42.019 --> 01:33:44.955
She won't trust an Indian.

01:34:02.473 --> 01:34:05.743
[**]

01:34:26.297 --> 01:34:29.600
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

01:34:44.682 --> 01:34:46.917
I want to buy two girls.

01:35:03.100 --> 01:35:05.035
I want to buy
two girls.

01:35:05.102 --> 01:35:06.704
ISAAC: Yeah?

01:35:08.839 --> 01:35:10.541
Do I deal with you?

01:35:10.608 --> 01:35:12.943
No.

01:35:13.010 --> 01:35:14.945
You deal with him, there.

01:35:42.640 --> 01:35:45.175
You have two girls
I want to buy.

01:35:45.242 --> 01:35:49.580
You are a make believe Indian.
Is that what you are?

01:35:50.381 --> 01:35:54.184
Yeah, that's right.

01:35:54.251 --> 01:36:01.692
You want to become a real
Indian? Like them?

01:36:01.759 --> 01:36:06.030
I want to give you 600 dollars
for two girls.

01:36:09.834 --> 01:36:12.937
Some here want your money.

01:36:13.003 --> 01:36:16.541
For the evil
your people have done...

01:36:16.607 --> 01:36:19.043
I want your pain.

01:36:19.744 --> 01:36:21.946
Look at me.

01:36:30.888 --> 01:36:34.692
Inside you are two dogs.

01:36:35.826 --> 01:36:39.597
One is evil,
the other is good.

01:36:39.664 --> 01:36:45.269
The mean dog fights
the good dog all the time.

01:36:46.604 --> 01:36:48.673
Which one wins?

01:36:49.774 --> 01:36:52.377
I don't know.

01:36:52.443 --> 01:36:56.381
Whichever one I feed the most.

01:36:56.447 --> 01:37:02.052
No.
They are killing each other.
That is what makes you sick.

01:37:02.119 --> 01:37:04.589
I will make you a real Indian.

01:37:04.655 --> 01:37:07.458
That is what your soul
asks me for.

01:37:23.808 --> 01:37:26.444
This will tear out your soul.

01:37:28.946 --> 01:37:32.116
[INDIANS CHATTERING,
LAUGHING]

01:38:18.328 --> 01:38:22.800
You were born white,
but you will die an Indian.

01:38:37.782 --> 01:38:41.519
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

01:38:42.753 --> 01:38:44.221
Ssh, ssh!

01:38:52.396 --> 01:38:54.699
Do you know this?
Do you know this?

01:38:54.765 --> 01:38:55.900
I don't understand.

01:38:56.834 --> 01:38:59.169
Die slow.

01:38:59.236 --> 01:39:02.740
The vultures will
eat your guts while you watch.

01:39:05.209 --> 01:39:07.144
Please. Please.

01:39:15.986 --> 01:39:17.788
That's my mother's.

01:39:17.855 --> 01:39:20.390
What did you do to my mother?
What did you do?

01:39:20.457 --> 01:39:22.226
[LILLY SCREAMS]

01:40:13.277 --> 01:40:18.849
[KAYITAH YELLS]

01:40:21.586 --> 01:40:22.587
[SPITS]

01:40:42.272 --> 01:40:44.675
You killed him.

01:40:44.742 --> 01:40:47.311
You killed us all.

01:40:54.619 --> 01:40:57.021
There is nothing we can do.

01:40:58.856 --> 01:41:01.458
There is no hope.

01:41:25.683 --> 01:41:26.951
[BIRD SQUAWKS]

01:41:33.490 --> 01:41:35.325
My friend.

01:41:40.765 --> 01:41:44.268
Do a favor for me.

01:41:45.803 --> 01:41:49.073
Forget your gophers and mice.

01:41:52.009 --> 01:41:58.415
Take me to my family.

01:42:37.421 --> 01:42:39.757
[BIRD CRIES]

01:42:51.035 --> 01:42:54.604
MAGGIE: Give them repentance
and better minds.

01:42:54.671 --> 01:42:58.876
Be merciful, O God, to those
who are in any trouble.

01:42:58.943 --> 01:43:01.078
And do thou,
O God of pity,

01:43:01.145 --> 01:43:02.880
administer to them
according to their...

01:43:02.947 --> 01:43:04.982
Ma?

01:43:05.049 --> 01:43:07.417
MAGGIE: ...needs.

01:43:07.484 --> 01:43:10.654
Grandpa said we was to leave
in the morning.

01:43:14.458 --> 01:43:16.360
He'll come back.

01:43:18.095 --> 01:43:20.831
He's gonna come back.

01:43:20.898 --> 01:43:22.900
Reward all those
who have done us good.

01:43:22.967 --> 01:43:26.303
Pardon all those
who have done or wish us evil.

01:43:26.370 --> 01:43:29.639
Give them repentance
and better minds.

01:43:29.706 --> 01:43:33.210
Be merciful, O God, to anyone
who's in any trouble.

01:43:33.277 --> 01:43:35.112
And deal with them,
O God of pity,

01:43:35.179 --> 01:43:37.047
according to their needs

01:43:37.114 --> 01:43:42.052
with kindness, just as
Jesus Christ, your son, did.

01:44:17.988 --> 01:44:19.990
I told you to go home.

01:44:20.057 --> 01:44:22.159
How bad are you hurt?

01:44:22.226 --> 01:44:25.195
I've seen the girl.
She's still alive.

01:44:31.435 --> 01:44:35.840
Your father never stopped
fighting.

01:44:35.906 --> 01:44:39.476
They killed him like cowards.

01:44:50.187 --> 01:44:52.056
Are we gonna go get Lilly?

01:45:03.934 --> 01:45:05.702
You can raise this child.

01:45:10.107 --> 01:45:12.142
Take her home.

01:45:14.211 --> 01:45:18.115
And you can be sure of that.

01:45:18.182 --> 01:45:19.749
You do anything else,

01:45:19.816 --> 01:45:21.919
you're likely to lose two
daughters and your own life.

01:45:31.929 --> 01:45:36.233
I don't know
how to leave her.

01:45:36.300 --> 01:45:38.002
You can't turn away from that?

01:45:42.372 --> 01:45:44.408
Can you?

01:45:54.351 --> 01:45:57.054
All right...

01:45:57.121 --> 01:45:59.256
Magdalena.

01:46:01.525 --> 01:46:03.593
All right.

01:46:11.969 --> 01:46:13.037
You.

01:46:16.073 --> 01:46:18.775
You scared of dead things?

01:46:36.426 --> 01:46:37.861
[SPEAKS IN APACHE]

01:46:43.267 --> 01:46:44.801
They finally
going to get buyers?

01:46:44.868 --> 01:46:49.206
He'll be back.
We sell them today.

01:46:49.273 --> 01:46:51.775
ISAAC: Hey, my friend,
we're getting paid today.

01:47:10.594 --> 01:47:13.530
The body is gone.

01:47:29.046 --> 01:47:31.015
It's him, look!

01:47:37.054 --> 01:47:38.822
He's come back from the dead!

01:47:38.888 --> 01:47:42.426
Don't think like that.
Come this way with me.

01:48:21.098 --> 01:48:22.332
It's a trick, you idiots!

01:49:01.171 --> 01:49:03.006
Get the girl.

01:49:51.821 --> 01:49:53.157
Get down there.

01:50:00.697 --> 01:50:03.032
[SPEAKS IN APACHE]

01:50:05.969 --> 01:50:07.036
Mama.

01:50:13.109 --> 01:50:16.146
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

01:50:16.213 --> 01:50:18.415
It's all right, baby.
It's all right.

01:50:21.285 --> 01:50:22.619
[GUNSHOT]

01:50:25.855 --> 01:50:28.225
You cut them loose.
Get to the horses!

01:50:44.107 --> 01:50:46.042
I thought we killed that
bastard.

01:50:55.819 --> 01:50:57.120
Get going!

01:51:15.739 --> 01:51:16.873
Get out of here, Maggie.

01:51:41.565 --> 01:51:42.799
Hyah!

01:51:42.866 --> 01:51:44.701
[WHISTLES]

01:52:38.021 --> 01:52:41.358
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

01:52:53.370 --> 01:52:56.272
Where are the women?

01:52:58.675 --> 01:53:02.679
Give me your horses.

01:53:02.746 --> 01:53:05.549
I will bring them back
before nightfall.

01:53:05.615 --> 01:53:09.786
And leave us here
with no horses?

01:53:09.853 --> 01:53:13.490
[LAUGHING]

01:53:15.191 --> 01:53:16.259
[MOCKING LAUGH]

01:53:41.651 --> 01:53:45.121
We don't have time
to drink water. Let's go!

01:53:53.530 --> 01:53:54.764
Can they catch us?

01:53:54.831 --> 01:53:56.533
Oh, yeah.

01:54:29.332 --> 01:54:30.967
Help me.

01:54:33.302 --> 01:54:34.370
MAGGIE: Take my arm.

01:54:35.405 --> 01:54:37.140
I got her.

01:54:59.062 --> 01:55:00.464
We're going to the top!

01:55:00.530 --> 01:55:02.999
If your horse quits,
get off and go on afoot!

01:55:26.490 --> 01:55:28.592
Hold on to the tail.
I got you.

01:56:05.061 --> 01:56:06.530
You knew this was here.

01:56:06.596 --> 01:56:08.565
I've had occasion
to use it before.

01:56:08.632 --> 01:56:10.734
We'll never make it over to
the other side before dark.

01:56:10.800 --> 01:56:13.637
We'll have to last out
the night right here.

01:56:18.341 --> 01:56:20.977
Put as much dry brush
as you can carry in this gap!

01:56:21.044 --> 01:56:22.946
Are you all right?

01:56:25.749 --> 01:56:27.717
Your hair's all tangled.

01:56:29.953 --> 01:56:32.622
Here, let me get it.

01:56:37.093 --> 01:56:40.263
[SOBBING]

01:56:40.329 --> 01:56:42.799
It's all right.

01:56:42.866 --> 01:56:44.067
It's all right.

01:56:47.671 --> 01:56:49.038
It's all right, Lill-Lill.

01:56:49.939 --> 01:56:52.375
You'll see.

01:56:52.441 --> 01:56:54.644
I dreamed on it.

01:56:55.845 --> 01:56:57.581
We're gonna get away,

01:56:57.647 --> 01:56:59.215
and Grandpa's gonna
come live with us

01:56:59.282 --> 01:57:01.317
and we're all
gonna be a family.

01:57:02.652 --> 01:57:05.088
You'll see.

01:57:05.154 --> 01:57:08.324
Right, Ma?
Isn't that right?

01:57:10.694 --> 01:57:12.395
Yeah.

01:57:25.709 --> 01:57:28.578
[CHIDIN CHANTING]

01:57:36.152 --> 01:57:38.588
[HORSE WHINNIES]

01:57:39.388 --> 01:57:40.824
[GUN CLICKS]

01:58:03.546 --> 01:58:06.115
Chaa-duu-ba-its-iidan.

01:58:06.182 --> 01:58:10.687
You know that Indian name
of yours?

01:58:10.754 --> 01:58:12.055
What's that mean?

01:58:12.121 --> 01:58:14.323
Very hard to translate that.

01:58:14.390 --> 01:58:15.524
Try it.

01:58:17.761 --> 01:58:20.596
It means "shit for luck."

01:58:29.639 --> 01:58:30.874
Is that right?

01:58:30.940 --> 01:58:32.842
Yes, it is.

01:58:34.110 --> 01:58:36.212
Chiricahua value family
very highly.

01:58:36.279 --> 01:58:38.214
A man doesn't live
with his wife and children,

01:58:38.281 --> 01:58:40.717
he's not considered
particularly...

01:58:43.519 --> 01:58:45.054
enviable.

01:58:46.255 --> 01:58:49.592
I don't have any Indian...

01:58:49.659 --> 01:58:52.061
brothers or sisters?

01:59:00.469 --> 01:59:01.504
None that lived.

01:59:09.913 --> 01:59:12.148
What did you see in them...

01:59:14.483 --> 01:59:16.319
you didn't see in us?

01:59:21.691 --> 01:59:23.092
Why didn't you stay?

01:59:30.533 --> 01:59:32.468
There's an Apache story
about a man

01:59:32.535 --> 01:59:33.870
that woke up one morning

01:59:33.937 --> 01:59:36.139
and saw a hawk on the wind.

01:59:36.205 --> 01:59:38.241
Walked outside
and never returned.

01:59:39.943 --> 01:59:42.178
After he died, he met his wife
in the spirit world.

01:59:42.245 --> 01:59:43.713
She asked him why
he never came home.

01:59:43.780 --> 01:59:46.716
He said, "Well,
the hawk kept flying."

01:59:53.189 --> 01:59:55.792
There's always the next
something, Maggie.

01:59:58.427 --> 02:00:00.596
And that will take a man away.

02:00:03.132 --> 02:00:05.001
You tell yourself
you're protecting them,

02:00:05.068 --> 02:00:07.503
they're better off
without you.

02:00:07.570 --> 02:00:09.705
Stay or go, there's
nothing a man can do

02:00:09.773 --> 02:00:11.975
to protect his family
from himself.

02:00:17.781 --> 02:00:22.151
I guess I do realize now
I made people's lives more...

02:00:22.218 --> 02:00:26.189
difficult by the things
I have done...

02:00:28.958 --> 02:00:31.160
and the things
I have not done.

02:00:36.966 --> 02:00:40.369
People I did love, mostly.

02:00:52.916 --> 02:00:54.650
I'm not forgiving you.

02:00:54.717 --> 02:00:56.252
Not asking you to.

02:01:12.902 --> 02:01:14.337
[OBJECT LANDS WITH A CLINK]

02:01:18.707 --> 02:01:21.777
I wore that birthing
both my girls.

02:01:21.845 --> 02:01:24.080
I thought I'd die wearing it.

02:01:27.316 --> 02:01:29.152
I've always liked this thing.

02:01:32.321 --> 02:01:34.924
Your mother gave it to me.

02:01:38.294 --> 02:01:40.529
Never meant to
leave it behind.

02:01:47.303 --> 02:01:48.504
Thank you.

02:02:12.695 --> 02:02:14.263
I better see
to Lilly and them.

02:02:29.678 --> 02:02:31.314
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

02:02:52.835 --> 02:02:53.937
[BULLET RICOCHETS]

02:03:00.209 --> 02:03:01.710
Look out!

02:03:05.748 --> 02:03:07.984
[HORSE WHINNIES]

02:03:09.385 --> 02:03:11.320
Pull those horses back!

02:07:04.520 --> 02:07:06.689
Your brujo's dead!

02:07:07.356 --> 02:07:08.524
Muerto!

02:07:12.995 --> 02:07:15.331
Fuera!

02:07:16.499 --> 02:07:17.500
Leave!

02:07:20.035 --> 02:07:22.238
Fuera!

02:07:32.415 --> 02:07:34.717
[SPEAKING IN APACHE]

02:07:56.405 --> 02:07:59.775
[**]

02:08:56.231 --> 02:08:58.667
[BIRD CHIRPS]

02:09:16.852 --> 02:09:19.288
MAGGIE: Let's go home.

02:09:53.489 --> 02:09:57.292
[**]
